  Step 4/8: Poll tasks/get until terminal — receive notifications/progress
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    Host ->> Server: tasks/get {taskId}  (polled every pollInterval)
    Server -->> Host: notifications/progress (1/3, 2/3, 3/3) via SSE
    Server -->> Host: {status: completed} on terminal poll

    The server streams progress notifications over the GET SSE channel
    while the task runs. Our notification callback (set up in Step 1)
    prints them inline. Once status reaches `completed`, the polling
    stops.

    Press Enter to run this step...
ERROR: RPC error -32601: method not found: tasks/get


  Step 5/8: Fetch the result payload via tasks/result
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    Host ->> Server: tasks/result {taskId}
    Server -->> Host: ToolResult

    tasks/get returns task status only. To get the actual tool result
    (content blocks, isError flag, structured content), the host calls
    tasks/result with the same taskId.

    Press Enter to run this step...
